verbs.description: unsort (third-person singular simple present unsorts, present participle unsorting, simple past and past participle unsorted)

entries.meaning: (transitive, nonstandard) To sort out; to resolve.
examples: In his letter to Virginia's governor excerpted below, Rolfe tries to unsort the mixture of motives that led to his decision to marry Pocahantas.

entries.meaning: (computing) To shuffle a data structure so that it is no longer sorted.
